In a press conference, President Trump announced his choice for the next president of the World Bank, Mr. David Malpass. Trump praised Malpass, highlighting his experience in economics, finance, government, and foreign policy. Malpass has been overseeing the IMF and the World Bank as Undersecretary of International Affairs at the Department of the Treasury. Trump also mentioned that Malpass has been a strong advocate for accountability at the World Bank and has fought for financing to be focused on places and projects that truly need assistance. Additionally, Malpass has been critical of the World Bank's Women Entrepreneur initiative and will prioritize empowering women globally. Trump emphasized that the United States is the largest contributor to the World Bank and that his administration aims to ensure that taxpayers' dollars are spent effectively and wisely.